caption: Delicious food, lovely cocktails, and super helpful and friendly staff. I'd definitely reccomend this spot to a friend.
Went here for a Sunday brunch and will definitely frequent this spot more and more food was delicious and the drinks were needed and spot enjoyed their Chicken and waffles and brunch punch

Excited they are open but This place leaves a lot to desire. Let's start with the host who didn't seem to give the friendly greeting. Then to the service. Our server seemed to take time to warm up. Not sure if it was just a long day. Then to the food and drinks. We ordered a Ceasar salad which was delicious but when I asked for dressing as it wasn't properly dressed they charged me for the extra dressing. Ok weird, I eat out everyday and never been charged for dressing. Then to the wings, average taste and fried well, not a fan of the quality of the wings. Sauce was amazing. Garlic parmasean to be exact. Buffalo was Ok. The ribs, they are worth it in size and cost. Could use a baby back instead of a full rib rack. Had a martini and it contained way to much vermouth. But my girlfriend was no longer hungry when we left so good job.
Excellent food, atmosphere & staff!
The food was outstanding and the prices were great too. All around great spot. Will definitely be coming back.

The Ryerson has been so incredible to our group of friends. We had a bday party in mid February and all of us have circled back in since at least once. We just had our 2nd bday party and everyone came away impressed once again by the excellent service, great food, chill vibe. Great neighborhood spot.

We loved this place because it was so chill. The music was great. The staff and service was excellent. The owners work there and Max was really hospitable and layed back. The mashed potatoes were amazing. Fried chicken is smoked then fried, I think, really tasty and served with three great sauces. String beans were delicious, out of all things. And the fish and chips were perfecto. Definitely worth a visit. Get the sangria pitcher with bourbon and leave happpppy..did I mention the mashed potatoes were amazing.

What an experience. Nestled in the trenches of my old hood this spot is a gem. The staff+ owners (matt and max) was the most hospitable and the food...O my, the food. The menu is submerged in comfort food from gravy boats to blue berry honey sauce. And make sure you try the fried chicken. Lawd!!!
Went here on 2/13/2021 with my family. Great customer service and tasty food. Definitely will be coming back.
Good little vibe. Burger was really good, just wish it was bigger. Service def a 10/10
Everything I've ever had here is so good. One of the best spots in crown heights! And their back patio is pretty warm even on cold days

Excellent neighborhood go-to with outstanding food and cocktails. Outdoor patio has been updated to make comfortable, heated outdoor dining possible but safe. Staff is remarkable and welcoming! Highly recommend the vegetarian biscuits and gravy, waffle fries, and cocktails (plus, when on special- the portobello mushroom sandwich is the best i’ve ever had!).
I fell in love first visit. Food, drinks, and waiter was on point. Very welcoming environment.
Great little back patio and the best burger in the neighborhood! Plus, the owners are super nice.

Amazing drinks to go with some amazing food. Food presentation make it even more enticing and aroma that makes you want to try someone else dish. I've had both brunch menu and lunch and I can say it's a great place to have with a single company or group of friends and workers. Very accommodating as well.
I love the service and food. The fact you can walk in and feel welcomed all throughout the stay is what matters.
This place is great.  Food is good, fresh and reasonably priced.   Cocktails are the best and the prices are the well worth it.

The fried chicken was very good, crispy on the outside with a unique and cheesy herb seasoning, and juicy inside. Outdoor seating was nice. No issues with service, and the prices were pretty good too! My only issue was that the mashed potatoes tasted like those puréed boxed powder mashed potatoes. They did not seem fresh and were way over salted. They should have been thick, creamy, buttery and well seasoned without the excess salt. I also did not enjoy the tiny onion rings on top of the mashed potatoes, definitely left a weird after taste. Try the chicken and waffles or chicken and veggies, but not the mash. All in all, I would come back.

The food is phenomenal here, the staff is really dope and friendly 2 things thats a must The Cornbread and this Frozen Drink called Thunder from Down Under and if you a fan of oysters the fresh oysters are everything .
Good food and great drinks 👍
best fried chicken i've had in ages! crispy, spicy, not too greasy. biscuit and mashed potatoes were great too.
OMGI I love this place. The cute patio set up was awesome and the month watering foods, Yummy! The only issues I have was the mosquitoes 🦟 attacking me lol But in all I highly recommend 👌
Just go there. Tonight.
The menu and service were ahead of our expectations. We absolutely liked the ambience of this place. Great restaurant to take the family out for lunch.

The food here was delicious. I came here 3/15/20 right before restaurants only did pick up or delivery. The staff was friendly and the place is cozy. It’s a perfect place to come with friends or a date. It’s very intimate here. The burger here is one of the best I've ever eaten it was so flavorful and juicy. Just thinking about it makes me salivate. The cheese, the bun, oh my. The deliver eggs were also delicious. We also had fries which were nice and the perfect crispiness. We had wine too. I wished the carrot cake was just a bit more moist. However, that citrus glaze with pecans complemented the cake very well. This place also has a backyard patio. Can’t wait for life to back to normal

The Ryerson serves up delicious riffs on southern cuisine. Excellent chicken, fish and chips, and, my favorite, etouffee, a deconstructed take on the Louisiana original. They also have interesting cocktails and a generous happy hour.
Great atmosphere, great cocktails, great food!
This is the ideal local neighbourhood bar (it's a shame it's not my local)
Great spot in the heart of Brooklyn.  I dont know which was better the fried chicken sandwich, the mashed potatoes, or the catfish !  Sean on the kitchen and Matt our waiter rock!!!!

This place is the one I like best. I go to a lot of restaurants but to this place I go the most. The stuff is very attentive and the cooking they offer is so good. I never miss an opportunity to have a decent dinner here. I highly recommend this place.
This place is the neighborhood bar of your dreams. It's calm, the food is good, the specials are excellent, the staff is friendly. Just do yourself a favor and go here one time. Have the burger.
Drinks were good. Food was HORRIBLE!!!
Service is great here Same with happy hour menu But the main dishes are not good: Fried chicken was really bad: bland , hard , and tasteless .
Top of the line
Very nice brunch with good vegan options.

One of the best restaurants in the neighborhood! Cozy and romantic ambience, an awesome southern inspired menu and tasty cocktails make this one of my favorite spots. Special shout out for Matt, he’s one of the best servers we’ve ever had- he really knows the menu inside and out. Can’t wait to come back in the summer to use the patio space!
The bartenders and chef attends to your needs and very courteous
They need a weekend oyster happy hour. If they had a brunch one I'd be there every time.

Everything about this place is to my taste. The food (New American with a distinctly southern accent), the cocktail program, the staff, all just terrific.  My wife and I ate too much and even as we laid on the floor of our living room, bemoaning our choice to overindulge, we were talking about what we were going to get there next.

This restaurant is my favorite place.  Of all restaurants I know I like it most. I never miss an opportunity to go to visit this restaurant. when  I feel like having a delicious dinner, this restaurant comes straight to my head.  Great and diverse  food and a large list of dishes.great staff members, and agreeable ambience. Not less important, the cost is modest. I praise this place with pleasure.
The food was delicious had both the  Chipotle barbeque and garlic wings. The fresh oysters we're tasty. A welcoming relax atmosphere.

Great local spot in crown heights. Their food is more "fusion" than southern from my perspective. Some dishes have really missed for me, but the hits are real hits. You can't ever go wrong with their fried chicken or mac and cheese, and they pull out some impressive specials.
Delicious corn bread, very good fried chicken sandwich and great service on a cold evening! A must repeat, for sure.

Deviled Eggs and Mac & Cheese apps were amazing as other reviewers have posted. Burger and Fried Catfish entrees were also delicious. Service (our server was Max) was spot on and everything came out piping hot. Nice cocktail list as well.
Great cocktails, better food, and the best staff and owners
The food was amazing and the staff was very friendly. I highly recommend the cornbread for anyone attending.
Great drinks, delicious food, fabulous atmosphere! Try the fried chicken and the mac and cheese. The Dr Feelgood cocktail is also a go to. Staff are attentive, knowledgeable, and friendly.
Hipster Bar. Unorganized bland and unoriginal

The place is super cute. Love the light fixtures. Great wine list. The white I had, I think it was last option on the wine by the glass section, Farscati (?) was absolutely lovely... light, a bit mineraly with a buttery finish.  The BBQ cauliflower was boom! Gravy with the fries was so yummy. The catfish is delish and well portioned. Great service. Will certainly be back!!
Wow. What a gem.
This place has no right to be this good!! Went with friends and loved it. Burger was great and everyone I was with thought their drinks were on point. Recommendable spot for sure.

Absolutely delicious!!! The vicar in a tutu is a phenomenal mixed drink, especially if you dont want too much sweetness. The mac and cheese is also delicious. The barbeque cauliflower was a pleasant surprise with just how well the flavors meshed. Highly, highly recommended!!

We had a wonderful time here. The food was delicious and the service was great. I don't tend to eat meat but i got the crispy pork belly and it was definitely worth it and super yummy. Also had the deviled eggs and the bbq cauliflower which were great as well. Definitely planning on coming back!

The food was delicious! The pork belly was to die for, and the barbecue cauliflower was so tasty as well. You can't go wrong with anything on the menu! The chef definitely knows what he's doing. Excellent service and an all around amazing restaurant I would recommend to everyone I know!
Fantastic food highlighted by a really great burger
Amazing. Fried chicken is incredible. Service is knowledgeable, friendly, but not overbearing. They make a great Negroni as well. Highly recommended!
An excellent burger and a very nice Cabernet Franc. Not too pricey, that's a +! Will definitely return.
Go to this restaurant!!!  Yes, get the chicken. Yes it’s expensive. But it’s a serving for two. Get the chicken and some other sides. Split it all with your friends / partner. Enjoy!
Delicious food, great cocktails!
My absolute favorite new restaurant. Everything they serve here is fantastic from the cocktails to the sides
Good atmosphere. Great food! Awesome cocktail!!

Get the fried chicken!!! Our server Bridget was excellent. The cocktails were delicious, and at a very reasonable price. Have already and will continue to recommend this place to everyone I talk to about great restaurants to visit.
Friendly staff, great food
Next level!!

Amazing restaurant with amazing food!Just wow!!! We had the oysters to start. Absolutely amazing. I had the burger, my god!!! SO JUICY AND FLAVORFUL! For drinks we had watermelon margarita and after that we tried different cocktails from their cocktail menu and they were all nice and strong! The staff was nice and overall the food and drinks were top notch!! Looking forward to come back and try some more food!!!
Everything was OK. Wish I'd the "pink" burger.
Great food, great service.
In the last year and a half of weekly visits to Brooklyn, this is by far the best place we've eaten. Warm and friendly staff...and incredible food. Try the fried chicken!!

The staff was very attentive and informative starting with the drink menu and specials. The drinks were good sized tasty and potent. The food was reasonable and excellent. This is a must go new place in Brooklyn!!

The Ryerson is exciting.  They've been open for 6 weeks at the time of this review.  Let's talk about the food first.  Overall impression: creative and justifiably ambitious. Case in point, the pesto mac & cheese.  Unexpectedly delectable.  The fried chicken was sublime as advertised - great breading in particular.  I usually don't put sauces on good fried chicken, but because this dish comes with a gravy, a hot sauce and a blueberry honey, I gave them a shot.  All 3 were tasty, but the blueberry honey is killer.  Finally, the burger is tasty and well balanced (though I wish it came with fries). The wait staff was notably friendly and attentive.  Nice and inventive cocktail selection, too. I'm looking forward to visiting The Ryerson in the coming years, and watching how it evolves.
Great food

This place is amazing!!! Outstanding delicious food. Anything we’ve ordered here was very tasty and prepared with dedication and finesse. Super friendly staff as well. Absolutely no complaints whatsoever. Pricing is very fair for what they offer and we will absolutely be back for more!!! They are easy to miss from the outside as the windows are very plain but the interior is elegantly cozy. Absolutely love this place!
Best new spot on Nostrand! Food & drinks were incredible, and amazing service. Will definitely be back soon!

Great music selection, AMAZING service. The owner is so welcoming! Thanks for opening in C.H. PS: The cocktails are just as tasty as they look. I recommend the Dr Feelgood for all those whiskey/fall season lovers!
So fun!
